<br>
Re: leaving one standing<br>
I've always done this as I was told early on that killing the room spawns that eeeeevil 50-something enchanter guy. However, I've seen plenty of cases now where the room was cleared and he didn't spawn, so it isn't that simple. I leave one standing anyway. Why not - it isn't like there is a shortage of spawns in this area.<br>
<br>
Re: drop rates on organs<br>
I don't think the drop rates are any worse than in The Grey, having fought in both. However, in The Grey there are shissar everywhere, and here you get one every 20 minutes or so. That's the catch.<br>
<br>
Re: the skull<br>
No idea<br>
<br>
Re: his other loot<br>
He drops a range slot item that is HP20 MANA20. I've been told this is actually fairly desirable for casters. I've never tried to sell on the market to see what it would fetch. Vendors buy it for 8pp or so.<br>
He drops a whip. The whip is pretty corny, and I don't think anyone would use it after a fairly low level. However, vendors buy this thing for 40pp or so if I recall.<br>
He drops Polished Serpent Scales. Dunno if these have any use, but vendors buy them for 20pp or so.<br>
<br>
Re: what level to solo<br>
I'd guess 52 or so. I did 53 and 54 here (and now part of 55). By 55, the only thing that is dark blue is the Taskmaster himself. But all his skeleton posse will still be light blue, and many of the random guys in the room outside his are light blue. The Stonegrabbers drop great cash. The underbulks occasionally drop claws which sell to vendors for 3pp or make very nice thrown weapons for monks. The fungus guys don't drop anything of much note, though they occasionally drop some pretty cool food or fangs that make decent thrown weapons as well. In the early 50's, be aware that undead or not, the Taskmaster hits pretty hard and very fast. I don't normally stun in battle, but I did him; attacking as fast as he does, stunning him for a few seconds removes a LOT of attacks. Bottom line: you may end up killing mostly light blues, but there are a LOT of them, they aren't tough, and they respawn quickly. Oh - the stupid pick that the skeletons drop sells to vendors for 10pp or so. Too bad it is lore or I'd be golden by now.<br>
<br>
Hope this helps, <br>
Zsa<br>
